background: A printing company is involved in producing math and English workbooks, with specific minimum and maximum production requirements. There is also a minimum total production requirement to fulfill a contract with a school.
constraints: Number of math workbooks is at least MinMath
Number of math workbooks is at most MaxMath
Number of English workbooks is at least MinEnglish
Number of English workbooks is at most MaxEnglish
Total number of workbooks is at least MinTotalWorkbooks
objective: Maximize the company's profit from workbook production
description: A printing company sells math workbooks and English workbooks. To meet demand, they must make at least \param{MinMath} math workbooks and at least \param{MinEnglish} English workbooks. However, they can make at most \param{MaxMath} math workbooks and at most \param{MaxEnglish} English workbooks. The company has a contract with a school to send at least \param{MinTotalWorkbooks} workbooks of either type. If the profit per math workbook is $\param{ProfitMath} and the profit per English workbook is $\param{ProfitEnglish}, how many of each should the company make to maximize profit?

parameters.definition: Minimum number of math workbooks to be made
Minimum number of English workbooks to be made
Maximum number of math workbooks to be made
Maximum number of English workbooks to be made
Minimum total number of workbooks to be sent under the contract
